1.title: The Departed, Part 1
1.plot: Guided by Bishop Heahmund's visions, the Saxons devise a battle plan. Ivar the Boneless strategizes on his own as the Vikings undergo increasing pressure. Bjorn Ironside finds himself in a new territory and must convince the local commander he is a trader and not a raider.

2.title: The Departed, Part 2
2.plot: As the Vikings establish their stronghold in York, Ivar is determined to lead the Great Army. In Kattegat, Lagertha misjudges King Harald and pays a heavy price. Floki arrives at a mysterious land.

3.title: Homeland
3.plot: Celebrations are cut short in the aftermath of the battle at York; Ragnar Lothbrok's sons are pitted against each other as tensions reach an all-time high, and each one is forced to choose a side.

4.title: The Plan
4.plot: Guided by Bishop Heahmund's visions, the Saxons devise a battle plan. Ivar the Boneless strategizes on his own as the Vikings undergo increasing pressure. Bjorn Ironside finds himself in a new territory and must convince the local commander he is a trader and not a raider.

5.title: The Prisoner
5.plot: Ivar meets his match in Bishop Heahmund. Floki returns to Kattegat. Bjorn receives a lavish welcome in North Africa.

6.title: The Message
6.plot: Lagertha is betrayed, and Bjorn must find a way to support the distraught queen; Floki and his settlers arrive in a new land, but it is far from what they expected.

7.title: Full Moon
7.plot: Bjorn returns to Kattegat to learn that an attack will take place during the next full moon; Ivar must decide if he can place his trust in a former enemy on the battlefield.

8.title: The Joke
8.plot: The battle for Kattegat begins. As the two armies line up to fight, the Great Heathen Army must decide between a final plea for peace or all-out war. Floki faces discord amongst the settlers.

9.title: A Simple Story
9.plot: The army leaders consider their options in the aftermath of the battle. In Floki's camp, all hopes of binding the community together are dashed as tragedy unfolds.

10.title: Moments of Vision
10.plot: A sense of doom looms over Kattegat as bloodshed ensues, but as the defeated army flees in the face of the victors, a legendary warrior makes his way home.

11.title: The Revelation
11.plot: Ivar is crowned the new king of Kattegat just in time to welcome Rollo home; Bjorn, Lagertha and Ubbe must rely on unsteady alliances to survive.

12.title: Murder Most Foul
12.plot: Bjorn, Lagertha and Ubbe face an uncertain fate as Heahmund's loyalty is tested; Floki fights to understand the will of the gods in Iceland; Ivar may have met his match in Kattegat.

13.title: A New God
13.plot: Heahmund must convince King Alfred that his actions are in defense of the crown; Ubbe and Torvi strengthen the position of the Vikings, but not all in the Viking camp support their strategy; another settler disappears in Iceland.

14.title: The Lost Moment
14.plot: King Harald and his army approaches Wessex while Aethelred is about to make a huge decision about his brother's fate.

15.title: Hell
15.plot: Bishop Heahmund is wracked with guilt as he fights to renounce his passions. Viking will clash with Saxon on the battlefield leaving a key figure lost in the balance.

16.title: The Buddha
16.plot: Ubbe achieves one of Ragnar's dreams; Ivar hatches a new plan in Kattegat, while preparing for a divine arrival; a settler in Iceland returns in a terrible state; King Alfred faces his greatest threat yet.

17.title: The Most Terrible Thing
17.plot: An unexpected turn among the settlers leaves Floki powerless. King Alfred confronts Judith. Bjorn must strike a deal with Harald. Wessex is once again threatened by a Viking force, but who will lead the Saxon army to defend the Realm?

18.title: Baldur
18.plot: Hvitserk is severely tested. Floki makes an amazing discovery. Freydis gives Ivar a surprise. Ubbe negotiates with the three Danish Kings that have massed their armies in Reading, but the negotiations may have a perilous outcome.

19.title: What Happens in the Cave
19.plot: Ubbe is forced into hand-to-hand combat. Floki reaches new depths and is met by a shocking sight. Bjorn sets off for Scandinavia with an old rival.

20.title: Ragnarok
20.plot: A new battle for Kattegat is on and only the gods know who will emerge victorious.

1.title: Rites of Passage
1.plot: Ragnar goes on a trip of initiation with his son. Meanwhile, he thinks he has finally found a way to sail ships to the west. However, his beliefs are seen as insane so he chooses to go against the law.

2.title: Wrath of the Northmen
2.plot: The stage is set for the first journey west by Ragnar Lothbrok as he gathers a crew willing to risk their lives to travel into the unknown.

3.title: Dispossessed
3.plot: A monastery in Lindesfarne, England is about to get a firsthand look at how the Vikings operate.

4.title: Trial
4.plot: The Vikings head back to England to see what other treasures this new world has to offer. This go round Ragnar and his crew sail out with Earl Haraldson's permission.

5.title: Raid
5.plot: In the Great Hall of Kattegat, a seer reads Earl Haraldson's future and tells him that Ragnar Lothbrok searches for his death.

6.title: Burial of the Dead
6.plot: Ragnar, weak and still hurt, must meet the Earl head-on after it comes to light that Rollo has been tortured on Haraldson's orders.

7.title: A King's Ransom
7.plot: Three Viking ships sail upriver towards the very heart of power in eastern England: the Royal Villa of King Aelle.

8.title: Sacrifice
8.plot: The traditional pilgrimage to Uppsala to thank the gods brings a torrent of emotions for Ragnar, Lagertha, and Athelstan.

9.title: All Change
9.plot: At the behest of King Horik, Ragnar assembles a small party to travel to Gotaland (modern day Sweden) to resolve a land dispute with the area's leader, Jarl Borg.

1.title: Brother's War
1.plot: The battle begins between Ragnar and King Horik's forces against Jarl Borg. Borg is joined by Rollo, and this Viking clash pits brother against brother.

2.title: Invasion
2.plot: Four peaceful years have since passed with Ragnar as Earl. The time has come for an unlikely alliance to band together in pursuit of a common goal - a new raid on England. A storm pushes the Viking fleet to a new destination, and on the beaches of Wessex, Ragnar and his men may have met their match.

3.title: Treachery
3.plot: The Wessex Viking raid is in full swing and King Ecbert finds himself facing an entirely new kind of foe. While Ragnar races to dominate in the West, Jarl Borg has his own plans in store for the future of Kattegat.

4.title: Eye for an Eye
4.plot: A meeting between two great men may pave the way for future compromise as Ragnar and Ecbert come face to face. Jarl Borg now rules Kattegat and with an iron fist and Rollo must now become the leader his people need in Ragnar's absence.

5.title: Answers in Blood
5.plot: Lagertha and Ragnar unite once again; Aslaug must face the truth of her prophecies; Athelstan struggles to define his faith; Bjorn must once again make a choice.

6.title: Unforgiven
6.plot: King Horik returns to Kattegat with a surprising proposition for Ragnar; Lagertha runs into a less than enthusiastic homecoming from her new husband; Athelstan becomes confidant to King Ecbert.

7.title: Blood Eagle
7.plot: Ragnar and King Horik clash over differences; King Aelle arrives in Wessex; Ecbert has an eye on a new alliance.

8.title: Boneless
8.plot: Princess Aslaug's latest prophecy comes to fruition; Ragnar and Horik have very different ideas about the true purpose of their trip to Wessex.

9.title: The Choice
9.plot: Ragnar's warriors march on to King Ecbert's villa and are met with a vicious surprise.

10.title: The Lord's Prayer
10.plot: Ragnar returns to Kattegat after the defeat in Wessex and places his trust in those who have stayed by his side all this time.

1.title: Mercenary
1.plot: Ragnar and Lagertha's fleets depart Kattegat once more for Wessex but this time they bring settlers.

2.title: The Wanderer
2.plot: Lagertha and Athelstan help to set up the Viking settlement; a mysterious wanderer turns up.

3.title: Warrior's Fate
3.plot: King Ecbert visits the developing Viking settlement as the first harvest is sown.

4.title: Scarred
4.plot: There is bitterness in the camp, Floki is angry over the alliance with Ecbert.

5.title: The Usurper
5.plot: The fleet returns to Kattegat to discover tragic circumstances await.

6.title: Born Again
6.plot: Preparations for the Paris raid pick up speed, and Rollo thinks about the Seer's prophecy.

7.title: Paris
7.plot: The Viking fleet causes panic in Paris; the Emperor Charles declares he will remain in the city.

8.title: To the Gates!
8.plot: The Viking army sets out and Paris goes into lockdown as the army prepares the defense.

9.title: Breaking Point
9.plot: The Vikings hit Paris with a second assault; Emperor Charles has to make a difficult decision.

10.title: The Dead
10.plot: With one last chance to take Paris, Ragnar and his Viking troops take a daring chance. Ragnar asks Bjorn for a favor that could change the course of Viking history.

1.title: A Good Treason
1.plot: As Ragnar lies in his sick bed in Kattegat, events unfold beyond his control.

2.title: Kill the Queen
2.plot: Ragnar and Floki are still at odds; Rollo makes great attempts to win over his new bride, Princess Gisla; Bjorn's survival skills are put to the test; King Ecbert sets the task for his son Aethelwulf to rescue Queen Kwenthrith.

3.title: Mercy
3.plot: Ragnar tells Floki he has to pay a heavy price for his actions. Rollo finds an ally in Count Odo. Bjorn Ironside finds more than he bargained for in the wilderness.

4.title: Yol
4.plot: Ragnar gets to know the new slave woman while Rollo reveals his ambitions to his wife. Bjorn meets an unexpected warrior on his way home.

5.title: Promised
5.plot: Halfdan the Black arrives in Kattegat. Floki reveals a secret to Finehair. Ragnar and Yidu become closer. Meanwhile Lagertha settles a score.

6.title: What Might Have Been
6.plot: Ragnar reveals his plan to raid Paris again, and although the fleet is storm-tossed as it sets out, the challenge lies in Frankia where Rollo awaits. Meanwhile, Ecbert dispatches Aethelwulf and Alfred on a pilgrimage to Rome.

7.title: The Profit and the Loss
7.plot: Now aware that Rollo has betrayed him, Ragnar carries out his plan of attack, which has dire consequences. Ecbert is given an offer from Prince Wigstan of Mercia. Harbard causes a stir with the women of Kattegat.

8.title: Portage
8.plot: After facing defeat on the river, Ragnar refuses to retreat, prompting him to change his methods of attacking Paris. Count Odo's plot against Charles and Rollo backfires. Ecbert now rules Mercia, which dissatisfies Kwenthrith.

9.title: Death All 'Round
9.plot: The Vikings finally reach the river. Aethelwulf and Alfred reach Rome. Erlendur makes his move against Bjorn. Sigurd makes a shocking discovery in Kattegat. Ecbert is crowned king in Mercia.

10.title: The Last Ship
10.plot: A ferocious battle between the Vikings and the Franks eventually comes down to Ragnar against Rollo. The outcome will seal the fate of the two brothers.

11.title: The Outsider
11.plot: Ragnar has returned to Kattegat where he devises a plan to return to Wessex to right past wrongs.

12.title: The Vision
12.plot: Ragnar seeks to equip his voyage to Wessex, even while being warned that the gods have deserted him. Bjorn prepares to fulfill his dream of exploring the Mediterranean.

13.title: Two Journeys
13.plot: Ragnar and Ivar face a difficult decision in regards to their crew; Bjorn has an unexpected reunion.

14.title: In the Uncertain Hour Before the Morning
14.plot: Lagertha attempts to fulfill a long-held ambition; Ragnar negotiates an unexpected concession from King Ecbert.

15.title: All His Angels
15.plot: King Aelle can't hide his pleasure when Ragnar arrives in a cage and shows him no mercy.

16.title: Crossings
16.plot: Bjorn's fleet sails onward and launches a surprise attack. Back in Kattegat, Lagertha continues in her quest for power.

17.title: The Great Army
17.plot: The Great Army is gathering in Kattegat, as Lagertha is saved by Bjorn Ironside from the hands of Ragnar's sons. Rollo is establishing the kingdom of Normandie as a safe-heaven for all vikings in search for land.

18.title: Revenge
18.plot: Ragnar's plan comes to fruition; the Viking army lands on the coast of Northumbria.

19.title: On the Eve
19.plot: The Viking army causes panic in the English countryside as King Ecbert and Aethelwulf plan the defense of the Kingdom of Wessex.

20.title: The Reckoning
20.plot: Prince Aethelwulf finds himself subject to the Vikings' battle master plan; Ecbert remains behind with a plan of his own.

imdb.plot outline: The adventures of a Ragnar Lothbrok: the greatest hero of his age. The series tells the saga of Ragnar's band of Viking brothers and his family as he rises to become King of the Viking tribes. As well as being a fearless warrior, Ragnar embodies the Norse traditions of devotion to the gods: legend has it that he was a direct descendant of Odin, the god of war and warriors.
imdb.title: Vikings
plot: _Vikings_ (qv) transports us to the brutal and mysterious world of Ragnar Lothbrok, a Viking warrior and farmer who yearns to explore - and raid - the distant shores across the ocean.::ahmetkozan

The adventures of a Ragnar Lothbrok: the greatest hero of his age. The series tells the saga of Ragnar's band of Viking brothers and his family as he rises to become King of the Viking tribes. As well as being a fearless warrior, Ragnar embodies the Norse traditions of devotion to the gods: legend has it that he was a direct descendant of Odin, the god of war and warriors.::History Channel

The story of how Ragnar Lothbrok, a Norse farmer with a thirst for exploration, who becomes the king of the northmen. Lothbrok, clouded by ambition and an urge to attain supremacy leads his men and his family to glory in the historic lands of Britain and France.::Archit srivastava

The story of Ragnar Lothbrok who, in the 9th century, rises from simple farmer to King of the _Vikings_ (qv). Along the way he deals with internal crises, family issues and foreign foes, and discovers a few new lands.::grantss
